==English==
{{wikipedia|Meriam people}}
===Etymology===
From [[Mer]] ([[Murray Island]]), off the northern coast of Australia.

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# An [[aboriginal]] [[people]] who live on [[Mer]] (Murray Island), in the eastern group of [[Torres Strait]] Islands off the northern tip of [[Australia]].
# The [[language]] of the Meriam people.

====Trivia====
The Meriam people are perhaps best known for their involvement in the High Court of Australia's [[w:Mabo decision|Mabo decision]] which fundamentally changed land law in Australia - recognising Aboriginal traditional ownership.